1
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:20,112
Host: sitting in a room in the basement of a building in central London with an Oxford academic who's an expert on war.

2
00:00:20,922 --> 00:00:22,525
Games Master: So my name's Dr Rob Johnson.

3
00:00:24,044 --> 00:00:28,921
Games Master: My area of research is about decision -making in crises and in conflicts.

4
00:00:33,460 --> 00:00:40,598
Host: Rob Johnson is showing me a piece of his own family's wartime history. It's something he always keeps with him.

5
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:48,445
Games Master: In front of me I've got my grandpa, this pocket watch, which he carried during the battle in Atlantic and the battle in the Mediterranean at Malta.

6
00:00:48,817 --> 00:00:52,664
Games Master: And this pocket watch was going to my father and subsequently to me.

7
00:00:55,870 --> 00:01:01,388
Host: Reginald Johnson had been a Shakespearean actor before the Second World War broke out.

8
00:01:03,008 --> 00:01:07,278
Host: Like most of his generation, he put his own dreams on hold

9
00:01:07,548 --> 00:01:10,720
Host: serve the nation in its time of crisis.

10
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:16,036
